We are so excited to welcome Chef Christophe Rull to the Sugar Geek Show family! ✨

Christophe will be teaching us all about pastry, sugar, and chocolate! He's a wealth of information with tips and techniques you wouldn't normally know about unless you've had formal training. 

The first season is all about CHOCOLATE and it's coming soon! What are you most excited to learn? 😁

In the meantime, don't forget to watch Christophe on the new Netflix show, Bake Squad, and follow him on his IG @chefchristopherull

Who else is excited about blackberry season?! 🙋🏻‍♀️ Fair warning, though... blackberries in your desserts can be tricky! They can easily turn from that beautiful purple/black color to green. 🤔💚

Pro-Tip: When the acidic blackberries bake with baking powder, they oxidize and turn green. Lowering the alkalinity of the batter and using baking soda instead kept the blackberries that nice, deep purple/red color. For an even deeper purple, you can add a few drops of violet food coloring to the puree. SCIENCE!

✖️NEW✖️ Come bake this ice cream cake with me! 🍨🇺🇸 

Are you planning to make ice cream cake this summer? 

Cut yourself a slice of this yummy, frozen treat this summer! This red, white, and blue ice cream cake is such a fun, cold dessert that will be perfect for your summer party! Every 4th of July we have a BBQ at our home with all our friends and their kids, and it's such a blast! Everyone brings a side dish and of course, I love to bake a cake! 🎂 🇺🇸 

⭐ PRO TIP: If you want to make this cake gluten-free, you can replace the flour with Bob’s Red Mill GF baking mix or another kind of GF flour like Cup4Cup. Just make sure your ice cream is also GF (check the ingredients) because sometimes ice cream contains wheat 🙌 

Head over to SugarGeekShow.com to save the full recipe and tutorial--link in my bio @sugargeekshow

✖️NEW✖️ Moist lemon buttermilk pound cake recipe on the blog! 
 
Can you tell I am obsessed with all things lemon this time of year? 😂 🍋  #whenlifegivesyoulemonsmakelemonglaze

This lemon buttermilk pound cake is tender, moist, and is the perfect easy cake to throw together for a last-minute gathering, brunch, or spring dessert! 

And yes, you CAN use a bundt cake pan for this recipe! Which is so awesome! If you use this lemon pound cake recipe in a bundt cake pan, I would just double the recipe to make sure you have enough batter and it will take a little longer to bake.

Also, if you don't have buttermilk that is perfectly fine! If I am ever in a pinch and don't have any buttermilk in my fridge, I will use regular milk plus 2 Tablespoons of white vinegar as a buttermilk substitute. 👍 🥛 

If you're a sucker for lemon like I am, you will ✨LOVE✨ this pound cake recipe! Jump over to the blog right now at sugargeekshow.com to try this recipe! Link in my bio @sugargeekshow

Light and crisp on the outside and soft and chewy in the center, these strawberry macarons would make an ✨ awesome homemade gift ✨ for Mother's Day! 

Sugar Geek Tip: if you're making these for Mother's Day, they can last about 2-3 days in the fridge. In fact, it is recommended that macarons be stored in the fridge for at least 24 hours to improve the texture of the cookie. Just something to keep in mind as you plan for this weekend! 

I've put together a step-by-step recipe over on sugargeekshow.com that will walk you through exactly how to make your very own strawberry macarons. And these are SO good you simply have to try them! 🍓 😍

See the full recipe over on my blog at www.sugargeekshow.com

Have you made ermine frosting before? 🎂 I know what you're thinking...boiled milk frosting? That sounds weird Liz. But, it's delicious and a lot easier to make than you'd think! ⁠
⁠
It's really simple and I promise, if you follow my recipe, you will have incredibly light frosting that almost reminds you of that frosting that you find in a ding dong or twinkie (but better!) This frosting doesn't have eggs in it, so it’s a fantastic alternative to Swiss meringue buttercream if you want a light frosting but can’t have eggs. ⁠
⁠
Head on over to my blog at www.sugargeekshow.com to get the full recipe Link in bio @sugargeekshow ⁠
⁠
https://sugargeekshow.com/recipe/ermine-frosting/

The real star of the show is the lime curd, though! If you're a citrus lover like me, you'll want to just eat that straight with a spoon! 😂

Watch the tutorial on my YouTube channel and get the recipe on www.sugargeekshow.com

What's your bagel order? Do you love an everything bagel with veggie cream cheese? Or are you more of a cinnamon sugar bagel with melted butter person? 

No matter how you knead it, my easy homemade bagel recipe is perfect for *anyone* who wants to bake and customize their own bagels! 🥯 

If you haven't made your own bagels yet, this is your sign! Making bagel dough at home has never been easier. Step-by-step instructions on my blog make it so easy! See the full recipe on my blog at sugargeekshow.com Link in bio @sugargeekshow

Does your family go apple picking? 🍏 🌳 ⁠
⁠
If you're planning on going apple picking at the end of this summer or the beginning of fall, here are some of the best apples to choose for apple pie:⁠
⁠
Jonagold – Slightly tart, crisp and holds its shape well after baking.⁠
Honeycrisp – Crisp, sweet, holds its shape well after baking.⁠
Braeburn – Crisp, sweet, and very juicy. Holds its shape well for baking.⁠
Mutsu – Sweet, firm, and great for baking⁠
Pink Lady – Sweet, crisp, and firm. Great for baking.⁠
⁠
You can use any apple that you want, but try to choose apples that are good for baking and will hold their shape! ⁠
⁠
Save this post so you can look back at it when you're picking your apples for your next apple pie, and tap the link in my bio to go to SugarGeekShow.com to bake my favorite apple pie recipe! ⁠
⁠
This pie recipe is ✨ so tender ✨ (never mushy), and has the flakiest all-butter crust you've ever tasted! 🥧 🤤  Link in bio @sugargeekshow

Do you want to know the top secret ingredient behind *why* this Oreo frosting that tastes like the real Oreo filling? Can you guess? If you've already made this cake, you may know the answer!⁠

Oreo filling is basically American buttercream. But what gives it that distinct, Oreo flavor is a little clear vanilla. ⁠

This is such a fun birthday cake idea for that person in your life who loves Oreo cookies! I've been tagged in so many beautiful cake photos that the Sugar Geeks have made since I released this recipe, and I am so SO happy so many of you love it! ⁠

node.text:
True or False? There is no such thing as the "perfect chocolate chip cookie recipe." ⁠
⁠
🔊 TRUUUUTH! *continues to yell into the abyss* 🤪 ⁠
⁠
Cookies drive me nuts. Can you tell? I can't stress this enough--cookies are a personal choice. You either love them chewy, or you love them crispy. You may love them with nuts, or without nuts. Heck, you may insist on your cookies being thick and a little bit burnt on the bottom. Whatever floats your boat!⁠
⁠
But, do not ever fall prey to the "perfect" chocolate chip cookie recipe. Because it simply 👏 does 👏 not 👏 exist! ⁠
⁠
With that said...I think I've come pretty darn close! 😂 ⁠
⁠
In my "master chocolate chip cookie recipe," I will walk you through what you will need to get your very own perfect cookie (because it's all about your own preferences). I share my tips and tricks when it comes to achieving the ideal textures and thickness, as well as how ingredients and how you measure them impact your overall taste. ⁠
⁠
Are you ready to roll up your sleeves and get baking with me? 🍪  If you're not quite ready yet, go ahead and save this post because it's a longer recipe with extensive explanations. Tap the link in my bio to head to my blog! @sugargeekshow

Who else loves Swiss Meringue Buttercream? 🙋 ⁠
⁠
Swiss Meringue Buttercream is light, fluffy, not too sweet...I mean, what's not to love?!⁠
⁠
You may or may not know this but SMBC is made from cooking and whipping up egg whites with sugar to make a thick meringue and then whipping in butter. It's great under fondant, holds up in heat better than whipped cream, and is DELICIOUS!⁠ I mean, ✨ so yummy and SO versatile! ✨ ⁠
⁠
Making Swiss meringue buttercream is not hard, but it can be time-consuming. If you’re in a hurry, try out my easy buttercream frosting recipe which uses pasteurized egg whites and doesn't require any heating.⁠ ⁠
⁠
Grab the recipe for my SMBC over on SugarGeekShow.com! Tap the link in my bio @sugargeekshow

This simple but effective berry wash recipe will help get rid of nasty mold spores and make your berries last longer! 🍓 🫐 ⁠
⁠
Use my berry wash recipe to get rid of nasty mold spores and make your berries last in the fridge for up to 3 weeks!! ⁠
⁠
Berries generally last anywhere from 3 to 7 seven days once they are picked and stored. It is best to refrigerate your berries, and in doing so, you will extend their freshness. Berries left at room temperature will continue to decay faster unless they are placed in a cool, dry temperature-controlled environment. ⁠
⁠
